e":285,"subtype":408,"resp":288,"ref":175},"Very fine to fine-grained, banded, white, calcitic (with dolomite) marble, likely Hymettan, Pentelic. Optical microscopy: heteroblastic to homeoblastic fabric with triple points, mosaic microstructure, lineated. Digital microscopy: indistinguishable fabric. muscovite (identification based on pXRF, digital microscopy, XRD, optical microscopy, stable isotopes analysis, EPR, LA-ICP-MS)","#material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Hymettan #material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Pentelic",[409,410],"Hymettan","Pentelic",{"ana":291},{"layout":413},{"p":414,"rs":415,"damage":416},"Five lines, approximately centred on the stone, except for line 5 which is aligned to the left margin.",{"_":38,"ana":39,"ref":40},{"ana":297},{"lettering":418,"dimensions":419},"Letters plain and somewhat crudely v-cut, without serifs, of regular height. Alpha with broken and straight bar; regular quadrate epsilon and sigma; theta close to rhomboid; mu with diagonal strokes, middle strokes meet at half height; nu with diagonal joining well above the baseline; phi is rhomboid and extended; uncial omega.",[420,423,426],{"type":44,"l":421,"from":46,"to":317,"h":422,"unit":47,"atLeast":309,"atMost":303},"Line 1-4","23-26 (omega 22, phi 36)",{"type":44,"l":322,"from":323,"to":323,"h":424,"unit":47,"atLeast":425,"atMost":319},"18-20","18",{"type":49,"l":50,"from":46,"to":51,"unit":47},{"_":428,"notBefore":125,"notAfter":337},"1st — 3rd century CE",[430,431],{"_":59,"type":60,"ref":61,"region":62},{"_":64,"type":65,"ref":66,"region":62},[433],[69,70],[],{"_":347,"role":348,"ref":349},{"_":437,"type":352},"35827",{"_":76,"mainLang":77,"languages":439},[76],"493015",{"n":139,"url":442,"height":443,"width":444,"desc":445,"surfaceType":144},"ISic001399_tiled.tif","2308px","3006px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Cultura